  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "2 Samuel 20:1",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Samuel 20:1",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "There happened to be there, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — His presence was casual in itself, though ordered by God’s providence. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "A man of Belial — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "A wicked and lawless person, one who attempted to shake off the yoke of civil authority. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "A Benjamite — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And therefore grieved at the translation of the kingdom from Saul and that tribe, to David and the tribe of Judah. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "We have no part in David — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The tribe of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Judah ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "have monopolized the king to themselves, and will not allow us any share in him; let them therefore enjoy him alone, and let us seek out a new king. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The son of Jesse — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "An expression of contempt, implying that he was no more to be owned as their king, but as a private person, as the son of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Jesse. To his tents — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Let us all desist from that unthankful office, of bringing the king back, and go each to our homes, that we may consider, and then meet together to choose a new king.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "20:1-3 One trial arises after another for our good, till we reach the place where sin and sorrow are for ever done away. Angry disputers misunderstand or misconstrue one another's words; proud men will have every thing their own way, or wholly refuse their assistance. The favour of the many is not to be depended upon; and what have others to expect, when Hosanna to the Son of David was soon changed to Crucify him, crucify him?",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
