        "text": "2 Samuel 20:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". There happened to be a worthless man there, named Sheba, a Benjaminite. He blew the trumpet, and said, \"We have no part in David, nor inheritance in the son of Jesse. Every man to his tents, O Israel!\" \"To his tents,\" i.e., to his home, as in ",
